about.description: castorapi is a python API wrapper for the Castor EDC API. The author is not affiliated with Castor EDC. Use at your own risk.
about.summary: Python API wrapper for Castor EDC to fetch data from your clinical study.

name: castorapi
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "castorapi" %}
{% set version = "0.2" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: "https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz"
  sha256: 75bb8bc4d935a80e5f7f091b0dae7214acb606f5d802b090bc253034da261820

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - json5
    - pandas
    - pip
    - progressbar2
    - python
    - requests
  run:
    - json5
    - pandas
    - progressbar2
    - python
    - requests

test:
  imports:
    - castorapi

about:
  home: https://github.com/wouterpotters/castorapi
  summary: Python API wrapper for Castor EDC to fetch data from your clinical study.
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  doc_url: https://github.com/wouterpotters/castorapi#usage
  dev_url: https://github.com/wouterpotters/castorapi
  description: castorapi is a python API wrapper for the Castor EDC API. The author is not affiliated with Castor EDC. Use at your own risk.
     
extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - wouterpotters
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.6.16
